App Challenge 1: The Classic Calculator7257

Tasks to Complete:
Construct the Display (QLineEdit)

Make a text field at the top that is read-only so the user can only change it by clicking the buttons.

Build the Number Pad (QGridLayout)

Use a loop to generate buttons for numbers 0-9 and arrange them in a classic 3x3 grid (with 0 at the bottom).

Implement Math Operators (QPushButton)

Create buttons for +, -, *, /, and =. Place them in the grid or in a separate vertical layout next to the numbers.

String Concatenation Logic

Connect the number buttons so that clicking them adds that number to the end of the text in the display (e.g., clicking "1" then "5" makes "15").

Evaluation Engine (eval())

When the = button is clicked, take the string from the display (like "15+5"), calculate the math, and update the display with the result.
